Text: Re StatServer Administration Cc LNotesnsf Mark I am looking into this Rabi Mark Fisher AM To Rabi NRON cc Patricia NRON Subject StatServer Administration Hi Rabi I am developing a StatServer Analytic but it keeps timing out at about seconds minutes In the page I am using I have tried increasing the time but it has no effect so could you find out if there is a setting on the server IIS script timeout and see about increasing the value Mark Fisher
Clear Sky ATP Cc LNotesnsf Patricia I have loaded all the MINANA and STATDAT files from the following directory Indian Mesa IIAprClear Sky ATP Thanks Rabi

Re StatServer Administration Cc LNotesnsf Mark I did not get the password David Miller and John Lapham said they will create a user with administrative privilege which I can use for administration In the meantime I will come to your desk to take a look at the problem Thanks Rabi Mark Fisher PM To Rabi NRON cc Patricia NRON Hollis NRON Subject StatServer Administration Rabi I have done some further exploration of the timeout problem on the StatServer I have tested the ASP page timeout and that does appear to exceed minutes Therefore the problem may be in the statserver configuration There is a setting labeled Request Timeout interval that might be causing the problem If it is set for minutes that would explain the problem Have you been able to get the new administrator password so that you can look at how the software is configured If this is not the problem could there be something limiting how long the connection to Oracle remains open Anyway a couple of more ideas Mark

Re February Mon Files Cc LNotesnsf Mark MON data is moved to Production Thanks Rabi Mark Fisher PM To Sunitha nron cc Patricia NRON Rabi NRON Mark V NRON Subject Re February Mon Files These look OK There are several problems with the data but they do not appear to be upload problems rather data coverage problems So these can all be moved to the production side Mark Sunitha Kongara PM To Patricia NRON Mark nron Rabi NRON cc Subject Re February Mon Files The MON data for MILL RUNSOMERSETKLONDIKE has already loaded into development database The data has been loaded for indian mesa for JanFeb directoryHow ever some turbines have less data because they do not having full month dataThe total number of records are The MON files of feb for MONFORT has been loadedTotal number of records are Please look at the data and let me know if any problems are there
